FBIS4-4505 "dreas063_d_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-063 Daily Report 1 Apr 1994 South Korea Reaction to UNSC Statement on DPRK Reported Reaction to UNSC Statement on DPRK Reported Government: Statement `Appropriate' SK0104022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0130 GMT 1 Apr 94 SK0104022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [Text] In a statement issued by Foreign Ministry Spokesman Chang Ki-ho on 1 April, the government appraised it was an appropriate measure that the UN Security Council [UNSC] urged North Korea to accept additional inspections and requested the Secretary General of the International Atomic Energy Agency report the result of the negotiation. The government said the UNSC presidential statement reflects the international community's deep concern over the seriousness of the North Korean nuclear issue and the resolute will to resolve the issue. He urged North Korea to immediately respond to the presidential statement.
